You know gravity as the force that keeps us
from falling off this planet. But it's so

00:00:07.380 --> 00:00:11.890
much more than that. Gravity predicts the
formation of planets, explains why they are

00:00:11.890 --> 00:00:17.500
spherical and why the orbits of planets around
the sun are elliptical. It helped us discover

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:22.689
one of the planets in our own solar system,
and the formation of Saturn’s rings. Gravity

00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:28.470
can bend and even trap light, and it governs
some of the behavior of the universe itself.

00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:32.529
In this video, we’ll look at the different
models of gravity and explore how each helps

00:00:32.529 --> 00:00:35.440
us understand these diverse phenomena.

